DONALD JOSEPH STRITMATER v. MARGARET STRITMATER [No. 16,

October Term, 1946.]

Decided November 20, 1946.

The cause was argued before Marbury, C. J., Delaplaine, Collins, Grason, and Henderson, JJ.

Marion A. Figinski for the appellant. Walter V. Harrison and H. Mortimer Kremer, with whom was Louis Samuels on the brief, for the appellee. Grason, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
